!!【柯林斯英汉双解大词典】

:<div>

transition /trænˈzɪʃən/

(transitioning,transitioned,transitions) 

1. N-VAR Transition is the process in which something changes from one state to another. 转型 

例： The transition from a dictatorship to a multi-party democracy is proving to be difficult. 从专政国家到多党民主国家的转型证明是很艰难的。 

2. V-I If someone transitions from one state or activity to another, they move gradually from one to the other. (逐渐地) 转向 [商业] 

例： Most of the discussion was on what needed to be done now as we transitioned from the security issues to the challenging economic issues. 大多数讨论都集中在目前需要做什么，因为我们已从安全问题逐渐转到具有挑战性的经济问题上。

</div>

